<h2 id="module-6-cloud-services"><strong>Module 6: Cloud Services</strong></h2>

<h1 id="hands-on-final-exam"><strong>Hands-on Final Exam</strong></h1>

<ol>
  <li>
    <p>Fork this repository https://github.com/ajcanlas-tip/sysad2-12021.git (Links to an external site.)</p>
  </li>
  <li>
    <p>Clone your new repository in your VM https://github.com/&lt; your username &gt;/sysad2-12021.git</p>
  </li>
  <li>
    <p>Create a branch named ‚Äúfinal-exam‚Äù and checkout in that branch.</p>
  </li>
  <li>
    <p>Create an Ansible playbook that does the following with an input of a config.yaml file and structure inventory file.</p>

    <p>4.1 Clone your prelim exam repository</p>

    <p>4.2 Install and configure one enterprise service that can be installed in Debian,Centos and OpenSuse servers</p>

    <p>4.3 Install and configure one monitoring tool that can be installed in Debian, Centos and OpenSuse servers (if it is a stack there should be option of different host)</p>

    <p>4.4 Change Motd as ‚ÄúAnsible Managed by <username>"</username></p>
  </li>
  <li>
    <p>push and commit your final-exam branch in the VM (no need for ansible.cfg upon pushing)</p>
  </li>
  <li>
    <p>request a pull request from that branch in GitHub</p>
  </li>
  <li>
    <p>For your final exam to be counted, please paste your repository link as an answer in this exam.</p>
  </li>
</ol>

<p>Note: Extra points if you will implement the said services via containerization.</p>

